In a #pot{} for the bulgur boil @water{240%ml}(salted) (double for 4p).

Once boiling stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pot and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Pick the @coriander{5%grams}(leaves picked) and roughly chop.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated), then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Finely chop the @baby spinach{60%grams}(finely chopped).

Halve the @lime{2}(halved).

Place a #pan{} over a medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%mins}.

> TIP: Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

To a #large bowl{} add the @peanut butter{2%sachet(s)}, @sesame oil{20%milliliter(s)}, @yoghurt{75%grams} and @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice).

Mix well to make your dressing.

Add a little water to thin it out if necessary.

Toss the pepper and carrot in the peanut dressing.

Add the chopped spinach and bulgur to the #bowl{}.

Mix well to coat everything in the dressing.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a generous squeeze of lime juice.

Divide the salad between bowls.

Scatter over the toasted sesame seeds and chopped coriander.

Chop any remaining lime into wedges and serve alongside.